{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Ari Lasso | image = | alt = | caption = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Ari Bernardus Lasso | alias = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1973|01|17}} | birth_place = [[Madiun]], East Java, Indonesia | origin = [[Surabaya]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) --> | death_place = | genre = [[Glam metal]], [[Pop Rock]] | occupation = Singer, songwriter | instrument = | Religion = Christian | years_active = 1991 - present | label = [[:id:Aquarius Musikindo|Aquarius Musikindo]] | associated_acts = [[Dewa 19]] | website = http://www.a-lass.com }} '''Ari Bernardus Lasso''' (born 17 January 1973 in [[Madiun]], [[East Java]]), better known as '''Ari Lasso''' is an Indonesian musician and former lead vocalist of [[Dewa 19]].
==Biography== Lasso was born in [[Madiun]], [[East Java]] on 17 January 1973{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}} to Bartholomeus B. Lasso and Sri Noerhida.{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}} His mother told him that he could become a famous singer, saying that "[his] life should be beautiful" because of his voice.{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}} While attending high school at [[SMA Negeri 2 Surabaya]], he established Outsider Band along with the drummer Wawan Juniarso, from [[Dewa 19]], and guitarist Piyu of [[Padi (band)|Padi]].{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}}{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}} After graduating from high school, he attended [[Airlangga University]] and earned a degree in economics.{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}}
Lasso eventually became a member of Dewa 19 together with Wawan Juniarson, Andra Junaidi, [[Ahmad Dhani]], and Erwin Prasetya. With Dewa 19, he released the album ''Kangen'', which was chosen as the best album of the year by BASF in 1993.{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}}
Beginning after Dewa 19's third album,{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}} Lasso used drugs heavily;{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}} his drug addiction led to him being fired by the band in 2001{{sfn|Simanjuntak 2003, Dewa buries}} and going bankrupt. In order to overcome his addiction, he tried going to rehab and alternative medicine; he was also hospitalized and put under isolation at home. All of these efforts were to no avail. After promising his dying mother that he would beat his addiction, he became more adamant in attempting to recover, eventually succeeding.{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}} He also quit his 20-year habit of smoking in 2010, after his son began taking and destroying his cigarettes.{{sfn|Jakarta Post 2010, Son motivates}}
After his dismissal from Dewa 19, Lasso became a solo singer.{{sfn|Simanjuntak 2003, Dewa buries}} He released his first solo album, the commercially successful ''Sendiri Dulu'', that year. Two years later, he released ''Keseimbangan'', which featured two songs performed with Dhani. In 2004 he released ''Kulihat Kudengar dan Kurasakan'', of which two songs became used for the movie ''Mengejar Matahari'' (''Chasing the Sun''). In 2006, he released the album ''Selalu Ada'', while the following year his album ''The Best of'' included a duet with [[Bunga Citra Lestari]].{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}}
In 2009 rumours spread that Lasso would become mute due to damage to his [[Larynx|voice box]]; although he did not perform for four months during that period, he performed in a series of concerts between May and June of that year.{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Ari Lasso}} Lasso has expressed interest in becoming a [[music producer]] if he can no longer be a singer.{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}}
In 2012, Lasso released a compilation album, [[Yang Terbaik (Ari Lasso album)|Yang Terbaik]]. The album was only sold at [[KFC]] outlets in Indonesia. The album compiled top hit singles and six new songs, "Kisah Kita", "Karena Aku Tlah Denganmu", "Cintailah Aku Sepenuh Hati", "Satu Cinta", "Doa Untuk Cinta" and "Cinta Adalah Misteri". Lasso also includes musicians who merged his albums sold in KFC stores like [[Cinta Laura]], [[Indah Dewi Pertiwi]], [[Agnes Monica]], [[SM*SH]], [[T.R.I.A.D]], [[Rossa (singer)|Rossa]], [[Slank]], [[Last Child (band)|Last Child]], [[Ello (singer)|Ello]], [[Sammy Simorangkir]], [[Armada (band)|Armada]] and [[Ungu]].
In 2016, Ari Lasso joined the judging panel of the [[The Voice Indonesia (season 2)|season 2]] of ''[[The Voice Indonesia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tabloidbintang.com/articles/film-tv-musik/kabar/31798-the-voice-indonesia-rcti-agnes-monica-judika-ari-lasso-dan-kaka-slank-jadi-juri|title=The Voice Indonesia RCTI: Agnes Monica, Judika, Ari Lasso dan Kaka Slank Jadi Juri|language=Indonesian|publisher=Tabloid Bintang|date=18 January 2016|accessdate=13 March 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life== When not busy with music, Lasso tries to participate in his children's lives, assisting with their homework and attending school performances. Lasso has noted that [[Mitch Albom]]'s ''[[The Five People You Meet in Heaven]]'' has influenced his parenting style and belief that a parent's interest in their children's lives can be a large influence.{{sfn|Loka 2011, Ari Lasso:}}
==Discography== ;With Dewa 19 *''Dewa 19'' (1992) *''Format Masa Depan'' (1994) *''Terbaik '' (1995) *''Pandawa Lima'' (1997)
;Solo *''Sendiri Dulu'' (''Alone for Now''; 2001) *''Keseimbangan'' (''Equality''; 2003) *''Kulihat Kudengar dan Kurasakan'' (''I See, I Hear, and I Feel''; 2004) *''Selalu Ada'' (''Always There''; 2006) *''The Best of'' (2007) *''Yang Terbaik'' (''The Best''; 2012).
