{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox person | name= Dira Paes | image = 26 Prêmio da Música Brasileira (18073035924).jpg | caption = Dira Paes in 2015 | birth_name = Ecleidira Maria Fonseca Paes | birth_date = {{Birth-date and age|June 30, 1969}} | birth_place = [[Abaetetuba]], [[Pará]], {{BRA}} | occupation = Actress | yearsactive = 1985–present }}
'''Ecleidira Maria Fonseca Paes''', better known by her stage name '''Dira Paes''' (born June 30, 1969) is a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] actress. Among the numerous award and nominations she has received, Paes won the Best Actress and Best Supporting Actress at the [[Festival de Brasília]] for ''[[Corisco & Dadá]]'' and ''[[Anahy de las Misiones]]'', respectively, as well as the Best Actress at the 2013 [[Grande Prêmio do Cinema Brasileiro]] for ''[[À Beira do Caminho]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/assets/Image/Direct/025860.pdf |title=The Dead Girl's Feast |publisher=[[Cannes Film Festival]] |accessdate=March 11, 2014 |page=6 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nz8J1Wxn?url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/assets/Image/Direct/025860.pdf |archivedate=March 11, 2014 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/grande-premio-do-cinema-brasileiro-2013-consagra-gonzaga-10775179 | title=Grande Prêmio do Cinema Brasileiro 2013 consagra 'Gonzaga' | author=Fonseca, Rodrigo | date=November 13, 2013 | work=[[O Globo]] | language=Portuguese}}</ref>
==Biography== Born in [[Abaetetuba]], in the interior of [[Pará]], and raised in [[Belém, Pará|Belém]], she had a very simple childhood with 7 siblings, and always wanted to be an actress, despite financial difficulties, she did not give up on her dream. She is a descendant of Portuguese, Indigenous peoples and Africans.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://guiadoscuriosos.com.br/categorias/2094/1/dira-paes.html|title=[Guia dos Curiosos]|work=Guia dos Curiosos}}</ref>
