'''Guanniu''' is a [[bull]] wrestling contest held in [[Jiaxing]], [[Zhejiang Province]], [[China]]. It has been a tradition of the [[Hui people|Hui]] [[ethnic minority]] since the 13th century. Local men test their [[Physical strength|strength]] against bulls weighing as much as 400&nbsp;kg. Contestants have to force a bull on the ground with their bare hands within three minutes.<ref>http://gbtimes.com/china/video-men-wrestle-400-kg-bulls-zhejiang</ref>

