'''Julio Navarrine''' (or '''Julio Plácido Navarrine''', December 20, 1889 - March 11, 1966) was an [[Argentine people|Argentinian]] singer, actor, poet and composer.

He is known for his [[tango]] lyrics, especially his song "'Oro muerto', of 1926, written in collaboration with [[Juan Raggi]]."<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of Julio Navarrine|url=http://www.todotango.com/english/artists/biography/1059/Julio-Navarrine/|website=Todo Tango|accessdate=30 August 2014}}</ref>

