{{Hazara people}}
'''Turkmun''', '''Turkmani Hazaras''' or '''Turkmen Hazaras''' ({{lang-haz|تُورکمون یا هزارهٔ ترکمنی}}) is a main and almost a large [[Hazara tribes|tribe]] of [[Hazara people]] in [[Afghanistan]] belonging to [[Oghuz Turks]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://afghandata.org:8080/xmlui/handle/azu/225|title=پژوهشی در تاریخ هزاره‌ها، نویسنده:حسینعلی یزدانی بهسودی (حاج کاظم)|last=|first=|publisher=چاپ خانه مهتاب|year=بهار 1368 خورشیدی|isbn=|location=Iran|pages=91&92}}</ref>

== Origin ==
Turkmun Hazaras share their history the as some other [[Hazara tribes]] with the [[Turkic peoples]] of [[Central Asia]].{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}

The main place of residence of these people was in [[Turkman Valley]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.co.uk/maps/place/Turkman+Valley,+Afghanistan/@34.7912687,68.5214276,13z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x38d23649725b9ced:0xf891f81ef15fb0c7|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|access-date=2017-06-22}}</ref> of [[Parwan Province]], but today most of them are living in [[Kabul City]]. Turkmani Hazaras have their own dialect of the [[Persian language]] known as [[Hazaragi dialect|Hazaragi]].<ref>Anita Jacobson-Widding. '' Identity, personal and socio-cultural: a symposium. Volume 5 of Uppsala studies in cultural anthropology''. Academiae Upsaliensis, 1983. {{ISBN|9155415008}}, 9789155415006</ref> hazaragi turkmani

